WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.407
Spare some change?

00:00:07.441 --> 00:00:09.176
Sorry, man,
I got nothing.

00:00:09.209 --> 00:00:11.311
All right.

00:00:14.648 --> 00:00:17.117
[siren wails]

00:00:19.086 --> 00:00:20.387
Hold it right there.

00:00:22.556 --> 00:00:23.357
[car door closes]

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:24.625
Let's see some ID.

00:00:24.658 --> 00:00:26.360
I wasn't even doing anything,
man.

00:00:26.393 --> 00:00:27.761
Are you talking back to me?

00:00:27.794 --> 00:00:29.763
No, I was just walking, man.

00:00:29.796 --> 00:00:32.099
Look, there is no reason
for you to get upset, sir.

00:00:32.132 --> 00:00:33.467
I'm not.
I'm not.

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:35.602
All right, that's it.
Put your hands on your head.

00:00:35.636 --> 00:00:36.770
Put my hands--

00:00:36.803 --> 00:00:40.274
Put your hands
on your head, yes!

00:00:40.307 --> 00:00:42.576
You had your chance.

00:00:44.478 --> 00:00:45.579
Listen, man,
can I just ask you,

00:00:45.612 --> 00:00:47.481
like, politely what it is
that I did?

00:00:47.514 --> 00:00:49.816
- Think I was born yesterday?
- Come on, man, I--

00:00:49.850 --> 00:00:51.385
Get in the car.
Duck your head.

00:00:51.418 --> 00:00:53.487
Aah!

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:55.756
Ahh.

00:00:55.789 --> 00:00:56.757
[groans]

00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:58.392
[bottles clink]

00:00:58.425 --> 00:01:01.662
All right, Officer,
I'll take it from here.

00:01:03.363 --> 00:01:06.733
Oh, hi, Wally.
Good to see you.

00:01:06.767 --> 00:01:08.802
He's all yours.

00:01:08.836 --> 00:01:10.737
All right.

00:01:10.771 --> 00:01:11.738
What?

00:01:11.772 --> 00:01:14.074
[chuckles]

00:01:14.107 --> 00:01:15.108
Y'all have a good night.

00:01:15.142 --> 00:01:16.276
All right.

00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:17.344
Thanks, man,
but where we going?

00:01:17.377 --> 00:01:20.747
I'm glad you asked.

00:01:20.781 --> 00:01:22.549
Follow me.

00:01:22.583 --> 00:01:23.750
Through there?

00:01:23.784 --> 00:01:24.751
[shouts]

00:01:24.785 --> 00:01:27.754
[magical tune]

00:01:27.788 --> 00:01:29.356
[laughs]

00:01:29.389 --> 00:01:32.826
Whoa, look at this place.

00:01:32.860 --> 00:01:34.228
Where are we?

00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:37.097
Just be patient,
and I'll show you.

00:01:37.130 --> 00:01:38.298
Your suit changed.

00:01:38.332 --> 00:01:40.234
♪ Follow me
to a place I know ♪

00:01:40.267 --> 00:01:41.768
♪ Where there ain't no pain
and no sorrow ♪

00:01:41.802 --> 00:01:46.206
♪ It's a place to be
if your skin is brown ♪

00:01:46.240 --> 00:01:49.776
♪ I'm talking 'bout Negrotown

00:01:49.810 --> 00:01:51.545
[cheerful music]

00:01:51.578 --> 00:01:53.113
Negrotown?

00:01:53.146 --> 00:01:54.281
What, like, Atlanta?

00:01:54.314 --> 00:01:56.250
[laughs]
Almost.

00:01:56.283 --> 00:01:58.652
Now be quiet while I sing.

00:01:58.685 --> 00:02:00.387
♪ In Negrotown,
you can walk the street ♪

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:02.189
♪ Without getting stopped,
harassed, or beat ♪

00:02:02.222 --> 00:02:06.693
♪ And there's always a cab
when you need to get around ♪

00:02:06.727 --> 00:02:08.095
And they always stop.

00:02:08.128 --> 00:02:10.697
♪ In Negrotown

00:02:10.731 --> 00:02:12.332
♪

00:02:12.366 --> 00:02:13.600
I think I'm getting it.

00:02:13.634 --> 00:02:15.802
It's like a utopia
for black people.

00:02:15.836 --> 00:02:17.070
Yeah!

00:02:17.104 --> 00:02:19.473
But seriously,
shut the fuck up.

00:02:19.506 --> 00:02:23.477
♪ You won't get followed
when you try to shop ♪

00:02:23.510 --> 00:02:25.746
(all)
♪ You can wear your hoodie

00:02:25.779 --> 00:02:27.581
♪ And not get shot

00:02:27.614 --> 00:02:31.451
♪ No white folks
to cross the street in fear ♪

00:02:31.485 --> 00:02:33.387
(all)
♪ No trigger-happy cops

00:02:33.420 --> 00:02:35.122
♪ Or scared cashiers

00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:36.256
(Jordan)
♪ That loan application

00:02:36.290 --> 00:02:39.293
♪ Can't get turned down

00:02:39.326 --> 00:02:42.229
♪ You're always approved
in Negrotown ♪

00:02:42.262 --> 00:02:43.564
This is amazing!

00:02:43.597 --> 00:02:45.098
I know, right?

00:02:45.132 --> 00:02:46.700
(women)
♪ We're going down
to Negrotown ♪

00:02:46.733 --> 00:02:48.635
♪ Where the strong black men
are raining down ♪

00:02:48.669 --> 00:02:52.773
♪ There's light skin,
dark skin, every shade ♪

00:02:52.806 --> 00:02:56.777
♪ And there's no white bitches
to take them away ♪

00:02:56.810 --> 00:02:59.179
♪

00:02:59.213 --> 00:03:00.547
This sounds too good
to be true.

00:03:00.581 --> 00:03:02.449
- It does, doesn't it?
- Yeah.

00:03:02.482 --> 00:03:03.717
But can a nigga
finish a song?

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:05.052
Oh.

00:03:05.052 --> 00:03:07.421
I mean,
can a nigga finish?

00:03:07.454 --> 00:03:09.456
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

00:03:09.489 --> 00:03:11.625
♪ In Negrotown,
you live long and well ♪

00:03:11.658 --> 00:03:13.594
♪ There's no disease,
no sickle cell ♪

00:03:13.627 --> 00:03:16.063
♪ No stupid-ass white folks
touching your hair ♪

00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:19.700
♪ Or stealing your culture,
claiming it's theirs ♪

00:03:19.733 --> 00:03:23.604
♪ Hanging out in a group
doesn't make you a gang ♪

00:03:23.637 --> 00:03:27.508
♪ Every word that you say
ain't considered slang ♪

00:03:27.541 --> 00:03:31.178
♪ No one trying to get in
on the latest trend ♪

00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:34.615
♪ By making you
their token black friend ♪

00:03:34.648 --> 00:03:38.485
♪ There's a place
where harmony is found ♪

00:03:38.519 --> 00:03:42.489
(all)
♪ It's a motherfucking
black playground ♪

00:03:42.523 --> 00:03:46.593
♪ Talking 'bout Negrotown

00:03:46.627 --> 00:03:48.362
(all)
♪ Talking 'bout Negro

00:03:48.395 --> 00:03:50.497
♪ Talking 'bout
Negro, Negro, Negro, Negro ♪

00:03:50.531 --> 00:03:57.738
♪ Talking 'bout Negrotown

00:03:57.771 --> 00:04:00.507
[song ends]

00:04:00.541 --> 00:04:02.509
[eerie humming]

00:04:02.543 --> 00:04:08.415
(man in the distance)
Sir? Sir? Sir?

00:04:08.448 --> 00:04:11.118
Sir?

00:04:11.151 --> 00:04:12.119
[groans]
Wha--

00:04:12.152 --> 00:04:13.320
All right, get up.

00:04:13.353 --> 00:04:15.155
- Wha--
- Let's go, get up.

00:04:15.189 --> 00:04:16.323
[groans]
Wait a second.

00:04:16.356 --> 00:04:18.058
Wait, wait, whoa, whoa,
hold on, wait.

00:04:18.091 --> 00:04:20.360
I thought I was going
to Negrotown.

00:04:20.394 --> 00:04:21.795
Oh, you are.

00:04:21.828 --> 00:04:24.798
[piano music]

00:04:24.831 --> 00:04:28.368
♪

00:04:28.402 --> 00:04:30.370
[door closes and engine starts]

00:04:32.206 --> 00:04:35.375
♪

